thread.title: Dallas Cowboys DT Tyrone Crawford doesn't feel like he's played up to his expectations
thread.title_full: Dallas Cowboys DT Tyrone Crawford doesn't feel like he's played up to his expectations | Dallas Morning News

author: Brandon George
title: Dallas Cowboys DT Tyrone Crawford doesn't feel like he's played up to his expectations
text:
IRVING -- In sports, more money brings more expectations. That's what Dallas Cowboys defensive tackle Tyrone Crawford faces now after signing a five-year, $45 million contract extension before the season.
In the season opener against the Giants, Crawford had a sack and three tackles (two for loss) in 44 plays. Over the last two games, Crawford hasn't showed up on the stat sheet despite being on the field for a combined 93 plays.
Crawford said Friday he's faced more double-teams this season but hasn't been pleased with the way he's played through three games.
"I feel like I've played lower than what I thought I'd be doing right now," Crawford said. "I definitely want to improve my game and step it up. I just need to get it together."
